Create ASP.NET Razor Pages C# application matching the functionality in Legacy-Screenshots folder.

Requirements:
- Target framework: .NET 8 (LTS) - <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>
- Modern, clean UI design (reference: https://cdn.dribbble.com/userupload/4279134/file/original-5e630140a5ad559268aaf9fd3650b403.png?resize=2048x1536&vertical=center)
- Index page with buttons/links for all database operations (add, read, filter data)
- Use stored procedures exclusively (no direct SQL, no table access)

Database Connection:
- Use managed identity authentication: Authentication=Active Directory Managed Identity
- Connection string format:
  ```
  Server=tcp:<server>.database.windows.net;
  Database=<db>;
  Authentication=Active Directory Managed Identity;
  User Id=<client-id-of-user-assigned-mi>;
  ```
- Do NOT use access tokens or other authentication methods
- For local development: Use "Authentication=Active Directory Default" (requires az login)

Error Handling:
- Return dummy data if database connection fails
- Display detailed error in header bar: file name, line number, and exact fix for managed identity issues
- Do NOT show code in error messages
- Errors must be user-actionable

Application must interact with database ONLY through APIs (see prompt-007).
